dc_title_s: France--north coast, approaches to Dieppe and Le Tréport (Raster Image)
dc_description_s: modified facsimile copy of French chart 7083, published 1988. Depths shown by isolines and soundings. Relief shown by contours and spot heights. "From surveys of SHOM to 1980." "Copyright restrictions of the country of origin continue to exist." "Soundings in meters." Includes origin of hydrographic information diagram and tidal tables. Map NO.37112 This map is part of a collection of scanned and georeferenced nautical charts produced by the National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency (NGA). United States. Service hydrographique et océanographique de la marine. Defense Mapping Agency. (1990). France--north coast, approaches to Dieppe and Le Tréport (Raster Image). LandInfo. Available at: https://purl.stanford.edu/zt999bj0324 This layer is presented in the WGS84 coordinate system for web display purposes. Downloadable data are provided in native coordinate system or projection.
dc_creator_sm: United States. Service hydrographique et océanographique de la marine. Defense Mapping Agency
